<HEAD>Four U.S. Presidents To Contribute To Book On Policy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STANFORD, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four American presidents and four Nobel
laureates will contribute to a major new book analyzing U.S. public
policy issues of the 1990s, the Hoover Institution announced.
   Presidents Ronald Reagan, Jimmy Carter, Gerald Ford and Richard
Nixon and Nobel laureates James Buchanan, Milton Friedman,
Friedrich von Hayek and Alexander Solzhenitsyn will be among the
authors, the institute said Monday.
   Other contributors to ``Thinking About America: The United
States in the 1990s,'' will include Secretary of State George
Shultz, former Defense Secretary Caspar Weinberger and Atlanta
Mayor Andrew Young, the former ambassador to the United Nations.
   The book is scheduled for publication in September.
