<HEAD>Sailor Charged With Murdering Paymaster</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAYPORT NAVAL STATION, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A sailor accused of killing a
payroll officer and stealing $94,000 from their ship's safe has
been formally charged with murder, robbery, kidnapping and
receiving stolen property, the Navy says.
   Petty Officer 1st Class Ruben Colon, 34, of Vega Baja, Puerto
Rico, was arrested April 12 aboard the destroyer USS John Hancock
docked here and informed of the charges Monday, Lt. Cmdr. Tim
Taylor said Tuesday.
   Lt. j.g. Ratish Prasad, 24, was fatally shot and choked and his
body shoved into a storage area of the destroyer on March 15, and
$94,629 cash was were stolen from the payroll office, authorities
said.
   Investigators reported finding $89,000 cash and blank checks in
a bank safe deposit box rented by Colon, a 14-year career Navy man.
Colon could be sentenced to death if convicted of premeditated
murder in a general court-martial.
