<HEAD>New York City Homicides Increase In 1987</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   New York City averaged more than four homicides
a day in 1987 for a total of 1,691, or 102 more than in 1986,
police said.
   ``We think there's a definite correlation between the increased
use of narcotics, particularly crack, and the increase in
homicides,'' Deputy Chief Raymond Kelly said Tuesday.
   He estimated that more than 38 percent of all homicides citywide
were drug-related.
