<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Germany-Escape,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>East German Escapes Amid Gunfire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 31-year-old East German man dodged
salvos of bullets to scramble over the heavily guarded Berlin Wall
and dashed unhurt to West Berlin, police said.
   West Berlin police spokesman Peter Glaser said the man used a
homemade ladder to scale fences on the East Berlin side of the wall
near the Neukoeln district before dawn Tuesday.
   He reached the wall under cover of darkness, but East German
border guards finally spotted him and began firing, police said.
West Berlin witnesses told police they heard three salvos of
automatic weapons fire.
   The man climbed over the barrier and dashed across a narrow
strip of East German territory to safety.
   Meanwhile, a 22-year-old East German border guard in uniform on
Tuesday escaped to the West German state of Lower Saxony, police in
Hanover said.
   They said the guard, a second lieutenant, fled unnoticed while
on duty.
