<HEAD>Doctors Donate Vasectomy to Public Television Fund-Raiser</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A couple's $185 bid was enough to win a
vasectomy donated by a group of doctors to help a public television
station.
   The procedure had been donated for the benefit of KCPT-TV by
Central Family Medicine, a medical group with offices in Mission
and Kansas City, Kan.
   It was purchased Monday by a couple who were unavailable for
comment, station officials said.
