<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Nepal-Earthquake     04-20 0125</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Nepal-Earthquake,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Strong Tremor In Nepal, No Injuries Reported</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake shook Nepal today,
sending people running out of their houses in the capital. No
injuries or damage were immediately reported.
   The tremor measured 5.2 on the Richter scale and was centered
around the town of Dhankuta, 188 miles east of Katmandu, the
Seismology Laboratory of the Department of Mines reported.
   The quake happened at 12:25 p.m. (2:25 a.m. EDT), the laboratory
said.
   No injuries or damage were reported.
   The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an
earthquake, as measured by the ground motion recorded on a
seismograph. A tremor measuring 5 can cause considerable damage,
while a magnitude 6 quake can cause severe damage.
</TEXT>
