<HEAD>Parents Sue Hard Rock Cafe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A $1.3 million suit has been filed against Hard
Rock Cafe in the alleged mauling of a 4-year-old girl by an English
sheep dog.
   Warren and Anne Balden alleged in the suit filed Tuesday that
Hard Rock Cafe International Inc., a restaurant manager and the
dog's owner, a cafe employee, were negligent because they allowed
the dog into the restaurant and failed to control it.
   The Baldens say they and their daughter, Elise, were leaving the
cafe on April 19, 1987, when the dog, with its owner nearby,
``seized the face of Elise Balden with its fangs, shaking (her)
body and head like a rag doll.''
   The suit said the girl will require cosmetic surgery. She
received 70 stitches at Presbyterian Hospital immediately after the
incident, Balden said.
   The suit was filed after negotiations failed to produce a
settlement, Balden said.
   Randy Roberts, a lawyer for the cafe, said Tuesday he could not
comment because he had not seen the suit.
