<HEAD>Police Battle Bangladesh Squatters, Injuring 30</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police swung bamboo sticks and fired
warning shots to put down a riot of about 500 stone-throwing
squatters, and at least 30 people were hurt, officials said
Wednesday.
   The landless peasants rioted Tuesday after police tried to evict
them from a site in the northern town of Rangpur, where they had
settled illegally, authorities said.
   Police acted at the request of the land's owner, according to
the officials, who spoke on condition of anonymity. The squatters
had been on the land for a week.
   Authorities fired warning shots into the air after their
truncheons failed to quiet the rioters, who pelted police with
stones, the officials said. However, the gunfire injured no one.
