<HEAD>California Governor Endorses Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gov. George Deukmejian endorsed Vice President
George Bush for the Republican presidential nomination on Wednesday.
   Deukmejian said Bush ``is unmatched in terms of the experience
and in terms of the leadership he has demonstrated'' and that the
vice president ``has demonstrated his strong support and loyalty to
President Reagan and to Republican ideals.''
   Deukmejian said he didn't endorse Bush earlier because he had
made a pledge to all the contenders for the GOP nomination that he
would remain neutral for the June 7 California primary.
   But only former television evangelist Pat Robertson remains in
the race against Bush. Robertson has all but abandoned campaigning
and concedes he has virtually no chance of getting the nomination.
   Asked by reporters at a news conference if he had supported Bush
from the start, or had favored one of the other GOP contenders,
Deukmejian said tersely: ``I'm going to keep that to myself.''
