<HEAD>Ted Turner Pleads No Contest to Importing Wild Lions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTICELLO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Broadcast executive Ted Turner pleaded
no contest to illegally importing wild mountain lions and was fined
$1,500 and ordered to produce public service announcements for two
wildlife groups.
   Turner, 49, entered the plea Tuesday in Jefferson County Court
to three counts of importing the animals to his plantation near
here without a permit. The offense carries a maximum penalty of a
$500 fine and 60 days in jail.
   Judge Felix Johnston ordered him to pay $750 each to two
wildlife groups and to produce one-minute public service
announcements for the groups at his own expense.
   The charges were filed last month after one of the lions brought
from a plantation in South Carolina was hit by a vehicle on
Interstate 10.
