   Construction of single-family homes rose
sharply in March for the second consecutive month, the government
says.
   But a steep decline in apartment construction held the overall
level of housing starts to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of
1.54 million units in March, the Commerce Department said Tuesday.
   Overall, starts rose 1.9 percent from the previous month.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Debt holders of First City Bancorporation of
Texas have submitted enough of their securities to pave the way for
a $1.6 billion federal bailout plan, the company says.
   Company officials made the disclosure on Tuesday regarding the
key debt buyback.
   The bailout plan calls for $970 million in assistance from the
Federal Deposit Insurance Corp., a spinoff of $1.79 billion of
poorly performing assets and a $500 million infusion of capital
raised privately by a group headed by Chicago investor A. Robert
Abboud.
