<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-DowChemical     04-20 0170</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Dow Chemical,0178</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Profit Doubles in 1st Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIDLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dow Chemical Co. said Wednesday its
first-quarter profit doubled from a year ago and credited increases
in prices and volume for the improvement.
   The company earned $507 million, or $2.67 a share, in the first
three months of 1988 compared with $246 million, or $1.28 a share,
a year earlier.
   First-quarter sales rose 32 percent to $3.98 billion from $3.02
billion a year earlier.
   ``Every business group contributed to these outstanding
results,'' Dow President Frank Popoff said. ``Demand was strong in
both the specialty and basic businesses.''
   The company said sales of its foundation products _ basic
plastics and chemicals _ set sales records of $798 million in
plastics and $1.34 billion in basic chemicals during the period.
   Quarterly sales of pharmaceuticals, agricultural, consumer and
industrial specialty products also set records, Dow said.
   Popoff said the company's costs remain stable and volume has
increased, adding there is no weakness apparent in the product
lines or geographical areas.
</TEXT>
