<2ND_LINE>AM-Reagan-CFTC,0097</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>West Named For New Term On CFTC</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan intends to nominate Fowler C.
West for a new term on the Commodity Futures Trading Commission,
the White House said Wednesday.
   West's reappointment, if approved by the Senate, would run until
April 13, 1992.
   Since 1982, West has been a member of the CFTC. Before that, he
was staff director for the House Agriculture Committee from 1973-82
and staff consultant from 1971-73.
   West, 47, graduated from Baylor University in 1963 and George
Washington University in 1980.
</TEXT>
