<HEAD>ITT Earnings Nearly Double in First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ITT Corp., the insurance, financial services and
industrial products concern, reported Wednesday its profits nearly
doubled in the first quarter, but said much of the improvement was
due to an accounting change.
   ITT reported earnings of $180 million, or $1.25 per share, up
from a restated $93 million, or 60 cents per share, in the first
quarter of 1987.
   The earlier quarter's results were restated to reflect a $67
million charge for an accounting change at ITT Defense Technology.
Without the change, earnings would have improved by 20 percent, the
company said.
   Revenue for the quarter ended March 31 were $5 billion, up 10
percent from $4.5 billion in the first quarter of 1987.
   The company's insurance and finance businesses rose 12 percent
and revenues on industrial products were higher, particularly
automotive, pulp and timber.
